### LESSON 253: SMOKE TEST — FETCH A SINGLE TODO BY ID
# Ids are generated via Math.random in data.ts, so replace the value below
# with one returned by a previous POST (see `new-todo.http`) or by the list
# endpoint (`get-todos.http`).
#
# Supplying an id that does not exist makes `getTodo` throw `Todo not found`.
# Express then routes the error into the global error-handling middleware in
# app.ts and responds with a 500. Swap the id for something like `abc` to
# exercise that path.
GET http://localhost:3000/todos/0.123456789
